The paper focuses on the design of opportunistic spectrum access in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), and computer networks and communications (cs.CR). The paper also formulates the problem as a partially observable Markov decision process (POMDP), which is a technique commonly used in control systems and robotics (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
